Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Over 30,000 SF of new retail/restaurant space nestled between the shores of the Gulf of Mexico and the pines of Point Washington State Forest in the heart of Seagrove Beach, Greenway Station embodies the casual elegance of 30A while integrating seamlessly into the natural environment that surrounds the area. Clean and contemporary, yet comfortable and welcoming, the development is perfectly designed to fit the coastal-chic vibe of the famous Beaches of South Walton. Greenway Station has been developed to serve the market’s desire for unique lodging in a mixed-use pedestrian friendly environment that pays homage to the area’s outdoor lifestyle. Centrally located along the renowned 30A and adjacent Timpoochee Trail recreational path, Greenway Station is a destination soon to be among South Walton’s finest lodging, dining and shopping experiences.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
REDFISH VILLAGE
Designed to keep nature a focal point of the community, Redfish Village is a unique setting and one of the most Eco-friendly environments along 30A. Making the most of the phenomenal location, this community is designed to evoke feelings of relaxation.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
This turn-key office has been finished with high quality interiors, featuring a large open floorplan, tall ceiling heights, a glassed-in meeting room, and a ground floor reception with elevator access. This space is now occupied by Vacasa, LLC
(international property management company with over 10,500 properties). Vacasa has executed a 5 year lease which began April 1, 2019 and is paying $98,000 net plus Association Dues & Property Taxes. The base rent escalates at 1% per year for the 1st 5 year term.
